# File Naming Conventions

## Kebab-case for all files
- Use kebab-case (dash-separated lowercase) for all file names
- Examples: `auth-service.ts`, `user-profile.tsx`, `api-client.js`
- Avoid camelCase, PascalCase, or snake_case in file names

## Specific naming patterns:

### Components
- `user-profile.tsx`, `login-form.tsx`

### Services
- `auth-service.ts`, `email-service.ts`  

### Utils
- `string-utils.ts`, `date-helpers.ts`

### Tests
- `auth-service.test.ts`, `user-profile.spec.tsx`

### Types
- `api-types.ts`, `user-types.ts`

### Config
- `eslint.config.js`, `jest.config.js`

## Exceptions:
- Standard configuration files: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `README.md`
- Framework conventions: `Dockerfile`, `Makefile`
- Hidden files: `.env`, `.gitignore`

## Examples

✅ **Good:**
```
packages/domains/auth/src/interfaces/graphql/auth-resolvers.ts
packages/shared/graphql-composer/src/schema-merger.ts
apps/auth/src/middleware/rate-limiter.ts
```

❌ **Bad:**
```
packages/domains/auth/src/interfaces/graphql/authResolvers.ts
packages/shared/graphql-composer/src/schemaMerger.ts
apps/auth/src/middleware/rateLimiter.ts
```

## Enforcement
When creating new files, always use kebab-case naming. When suggesting file names or refactoring, convert existing files to kebab-case format.
